Vision

KompozeR is a web application that extends the e-commerce platform of Kompo (www.soluzionekompo.com), a company selling modular and customisable furniture. It allows users to design their own shelving unit through an interactive visual configurator, preview the result in real time, and automatically populate a shopping cart with the selected components.

The project want to satisfy the requirements of two courses (Web Applications and Services and Distributed Systems). To achieve this, the functionalities were identified and, where necessary, extended in order to comply with the requirements of both courses.

The project for the Distributed Systems course will be extended with a collaborative editing feature: multiple authenticated users can design the same configuration simultaneously in real time, observing each other's changes as they happen. A central backend coordinates all sessions, maintaining a consistent shared state across all connected clients and broadcasting incremental updates via WebSocket.

Concurrent edits are handled through causal ordering of events, avoiding reliance on a global clock. The persistence layer is replicated, making the consistency/availability trade-off explicit and configurable at the application level. The collaborative session state is periodically checkpointed so that, in the event of a server crash, the system can recover to a consistent state and resume from there.

Concurrency is not limited to the collaborative editing feature: as an e-commerce platform, KompozeR naturally faces concurrent writes from independent users placing orders, updating carts, and querying stock levels against the same shared database. This makes consistency and isolation relevant across the entire application, not only in the collaborative context.

Learning goals

- Client-Server architecture with event-based communication
- Replication and consistency
- Fault tolerance and availability
- Checkpointing and recovery
- Causal ordering of distributed events
- Container orchestration

Intended Technologies

- Node.js + Express: backend REST API and session coordinator
- Vue.js + TypeScript: single-page frontend with visual configurator
- Socket.io: real-time bidirectional communication for collaborative editing
- MongoDB Replica Set: replicated persistence layer
- Docker Compose: local multi-container deployment
- Kubernetes (Minikube): production-oriented deployment 

