- Final report

Usage scenarios

- A user opens the application, logs in and creates a new configuration project, optionally sharing an invite link with collaborators
- Multiple users open the same configuration simultaneously; each cell edit is t broadcast to all participants, who see the change reflected in real time
- Two users edit the same cell concurrently; the backend applies ordering methods and broadcasts the resolved state to all clients
- The backend process crashes; upon restart it loads the latest checkpoint from stable storage and notifies connected clients to resynchronise, replaying any events logged after the checkpoint
- The MongoDB primary becomes unavailable; the replica set elects a new primary within seconds, and the application continues to serve requests with configurable consistency guarantees

